        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 4 at 9:55PM CDT until April 4 at 10:30PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>SVRLZK

The National Weather Service in Little Rock has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Scott County in western Arkansas...
Northwestern Polk County in western Arkansas...

* Until 1030 PM CDT.

* At 955 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Hatfield, or
14 miles southwest of Mena, moving north at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Black Fork...                     Rocky...
Black Fork Mountain Wilderness... Winfield...
Morgan Springs...                 Beauchamp...
Camp Pioneer...                   Acorn...
Hatfield...                       Mena...
Rich Mountain...                  Queen Wilhelmina State Park...
Mountain Fork...                  Potter...
Polk County Fairgrounds...        Cove...
Dallas...                         Eagleton...
Shady Grove...                    Mccauley...
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
